## Plan Summary

Here's the implementation plan for the `mistral-instruct-v3` template handler. **Only `common/chat.cpp` changes** — two additions:

---

### Edit 1 — New handler function (insert before line 825)

```cpp
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(
        const common_chat_template &          tmpl,
        const autoparser::generation_params & inputs) {
    common_chat_params data;

    std::string system_prompt;
    bool first_user = true;

    for (const auto & msg : inputs.messages) {
        const auto role    = msg.value("role", "");
        const auto content = msg.value("content", "");

        if (role == "system") {
            system_prompt = content;
        } else if (role == "user") {
            if (first_user) {
                data.prompt += tmpl.bos_token();
                data.prompt += "[INST] ";
                if (!system_prompt.empty()) {
                    data.prompt += system_prompt + "\n";
                }
                data.prompt += content + " [/INST]";
                first_user = false;
            } else {
                data.prompt += "[INST] " + content + " [/INST]";
            }
        } else if (role == "assistant") {
            data.prompt += " " + content + "</s>";
        }
    }

    data.format = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY;
    return data;
}
```

**Key design decisions:**
- Uses `tmpl.bos_token()` (not hardcoded `<s>`) — consistent with codebase patterns
- System message is stored, then prepended inline to the first `[INST]` block
- Assistant turns end with literal `</s>` (format spec requirement, not `tmpl.eos_token()`)
- Field access via `msg.value("role", "")` / `msg.value("content", "")` — matches every existing handler

